        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 12:53PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1253 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Aguilar, or 16 miles north of Trinidad, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Model.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
